Sec. 72.045. SEIZURE OF OWNERLESS FRUIT. If the department is
not able to locate an owner, part owner, or caretaker for premises in
a county in which Mexican fruit fly control or eradication is being
conducted, the department may seize any citrus fruit growing or
standing on the premises and sell the fruit in the manner provided by
Section 72.043(b) of this code.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1170, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.

